        My name is Jackson Behan. I’m a 28-year-old developer living in Albany. To be able to call myself that, a developer, is a huge accomplishment for me. I felt lost for a long time, especially in school, where I never found a passion in any subject. When I was 26 I discovered programming and decided to learn how to code at Dev Bootcamp in San Francisco. Within a month of completing the intensive course, I landed a job in Las Vegas. I was young, inexperienced and severely lacking in confidence, but at last, I finally had a real job. Two years later, I’m back home in NY and ready to take on new challenges.
